ce:section.ce:para:
The degradation pathway of CBF in the presence of visible light and InV/InS has been predicted based on the experimental findings (Scheme 2
                        ). LC-MS was employed to identify the intermediate compounds generated during the sonophotocatalytic degradation of CBF. According to LC-MS analysis, the cleavage of the carbamate group from the parent carbofuran yields 2,2-dimethyl-2,3-dihydrobenzofuran-7-ol, which has a peak at m/z 165.15 (Fig. 11
                        a) [54]. Then, 2,3-dihydrobenzofuran-7-ol (m/z: 137.15) was produced through demethylation of 2,2-dimethyl-2,3-dihydrobenzofuran-7-ol. The 2,3-dihydrobenzofuran-7-ol underwent ring opening, leading to the formation of 2,3-dihydroxybenzoic acid (m/z: 155.10), from which further decarboxylation produces pyrocatechol (m/z: 111.10). Finally, pyrocatechol undergoes hydrolysis into smaller aliphatic acids, followed by mineralization into carbon dioxide and water.
